msContents.summary: Manuscript of the Khordeh Avesta containing Avestan texts, some with Pahlavi translation, including Jasa-me, Afsudan-i Gomez, Kem-na Mazda, Nirang Naxun Pahrez, Niyayesh 1 and 3, Afrin-i Dahman, Afrinagan-i Frawardigan, Afrinagan-i Gahambar, Siroza Yast 1, and Yasht 1. These are followed by two Persian texts.
msContents.textLang: Avestan and Persian with some Pahlavi

msItem.title: Dar z̲ikr-i muluk furus az Ardishīr Bābakān tā Yazdgird-i Shahriyār

supportDesc.extent: i, 174, i leaves : 194 x 140 (140 x 90) mm, bound to 197 x 140 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Avestan and nastaʻlīq in black ink.

binding.p: Unstamped light brown leather over pasteboard; plain paper pastedowns. Cover is partially detached.

origin.p: Copy completed in Yazd in 1095 AY (1726 CE) by Rustam Gushtāsp Ardashīr Gushtāsp (f. 86v, 151v).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Sorabji Framji Madan (note, front flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by Mobed Hormazdyar Mobed Khodabaksh (note, back flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by Mobed Framji Fardunji Madan (provenance record in M.N. Dhalla, The Nyaishes or Zoroastrian Litanies, 1908).
